description:
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking to recruit an enthusiastic and motivated HR Support Officer to join our HR Team at CHCP CIC.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This varied and busy role will see the post holder working as part of a friendly and dedicated team. This post is a key customer facing role with the primary focus of providing a high quality and innovative recruitment service to all of our stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also provide comprehensive administration support services across the Human Resources function.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will provide general administration support as well as being the key contact for all recruitment queries from both candidates and recruiting managers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for ensuring accurate and up to date data is added to our computerised systems (NHS Jobs, TRAC, ESR, etc). You will have an excellent knoweldge of microsoft packages and be confident to use these on a daily basis, therefore good keyboard skills are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;You will need to have an understanding of confidentiality and data protection which is imperative. The ability to prioritise your own workload and be systematic is essential. You must have a flexible approach to work in order to deal with set deadlines and varying work loads. A high level of accuracy and attention to detail is paramount. In addition to IT experience, there is a need for excellent customer service and good communication skills as well as a confident telephone manner.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
